item.title: CVE-2023-0392|2023-11-08T20:37:14.786Z -- okta -- ldap%20agent
item.description: The LDAP Agent Update service with versions prior to 5.18 used an unquoted path, which could allow arbitrary code execution.

item.title: CVE-2023-0093|2023-03-06T00:00:00 -- okta -- advanced%20server%20access
item.description: Okta Advanced Server Access Client versions 1.13.1 through 1.65.0 are vulnerable to command injection due to the third party library webbrowser. An outdated library, webbrowser, used by the ASA client was found to be vulnerable to command injection. To exploit this issue, an attacker would need to phish the user to enter an attacker controlled server URL during enrollment.

item.title: CVE-2024-0980|2024-03-28T16:59:21.177Z -- okta -- okta%20verify%20for%20windows
item.description: The Auto-update service for Okta Verify for Windows is vulnerable to two flaws which in combination could be used to execute arbitrary code.
